<ul id="tab">
<li class="active">
<h4>regulations</h4>
<p><center><h3>general conduct on the blog&nbsp;&nbsp;</h3></center>
<p>Anon hate will be deleted without commentary, full stop. the feature, as well as my submission box, are currently enabled but I will not hesitate to close them & leave them off. I've seen how ugly things can get, & i don't play those games. my inbox is where hate goes to die tbh.

<p>additionally, <b>I DO NOT ACCEPT ANONYMOUS CRITIQUE</b> of my portrayal, my blog, or myself. I am more than happy to accept critique given off anon - it's how I grow & expand my abilities as a writer. I find that the anon feature enables more <i>CRUELTY</i> than it does productivity or constructive criticism, ergo without a face, it's just mean wrapped up in gift wrapping labeled "helpful."

<p>the anon feature is solely enabled for partners using sideblogs, or who have multiple blogs & may not happen to be logged into their blog of choice when they see a meme they want to send. if an ask <b>does not</b> have a URL associated with it, then I will likely delete it without publishing.

<p>this blog does not partake in discourse. I don't mind seeing it on the dash, but I <b>will not contribute to it</b> in any way, shape, or form, on my RP blogs as a matter of personal comfort. if you happen to have the link for <i>my personal blog</i>, you can find many of my thoughts, feelings, & opinions on a broad spectrum of meta - both fandom & rpc-centric - there.

<p>I practice <b>categorical denial of subtext</b> - I will not respond to passive aggression, silent treatment, guilt tripping, or other related behaviors - full stop. It’s 2020. I’m no longer tolerating this behavior in myself, & I will no longer tolerate it in others, either. If we can not communicate openly & respectfully, <b>then we will not communicate</b>.

<blockquote>
    <p>this additionally pertains to <b>exclusivity</b>. I will make no assumptions, & I ask for none in return - if there is a month or more of no ic interaction & no communication ooc pertaining to why, I reserve the right to open the spot up to someone else.
</blockquote>

<p>Finally, <b>I do not accept ANONYMOUS COMMENTARY OF ANY SORT</b> regarding my partners. if there is valid reason to believe someone seen on this blog is problematic, please come to me off anon - otherwise I have to assume there's an ulterior & shady motive, & will ignore it. tl;dr: start drama with me about my friends? <b>BLOCK ME NOW - WE ARE DONE</b>.

<p>For this same reason, this blog is currently MUTUALS ONLY. I am always down for exploring new plots & interactions - if we aren’t mutuals, you are still welcome to approach me with a plot if you have an idea for how our muses might interact. 

<p>There will be mature content on this blog, making it 18+ only.  If you do not list your (the mun) age on your blog, I will not follow you.
<br /><br />

<p><center><h3>disclaimer & general information&nbsp;&nbsp;</h3></center>
<p>This blog is a private & highly selective writing & graphics blog for <b>CLARISSA ADELE FAIRCHILD</B> of <i>the shadowhunter chronicles</i>. I don’t own her canon, & make no claim as such however her verses & portrayal are my own. My portrayal of Clary is heavily steeped in divergency & headcanons, meaning she may react with some amount of nuanced difference than how she might within the constraints of pure canon. This is especially notable in her <b>variant verses</b>.

<br /><br />

<blockquote>
    <p><i>most important</i>: I will not change my interpretation of my muse just because it's "convenient" for an interaction. If I start noticing that you’re ignoring parts of my character's canon because you don’t like it/don’t agree with it, I reserve the right to drop all threads without warning. I don’t write as much as I do on my character to have it treated like it’s optional.
</blockquote>

<p><center>while the above seems very harsh, this has been a significant problem for me on my other blogs so I've learned it's something I just cannot tolerate.</center>

<p><center><h3>regarding writing & interaction&nbsp;&nbsp;</h3></center>
<p>This blog is <b>PRIVATE & HIGHLY SELECTIVE</b>. it is also very <b>PLOT INTENSIVE</b>. I am open to both canon sources, multifandom crossovers, & original characters - I just prefer that blogs have a <i>RULES PAGE</i> somewhere I can find, as well as <b>AN ABOUT PAGE</b>. this is especially important for blogs outside of my canon familiarity & OCs - otherwise I may not know how to interact with you adequately.

<p>my preferred style is multi para* & novella (at least 2-4 paragraphs (~400+ words) vs. anything over 1-1.5k word length.) I primarily use icons & small text in terms of formatting, as well as <b>THIRD PERSON PRESENT TENSE</b>. 

<div id="left"><img src="https://i.imgur.com/pEMRlHI.png"> <i>important!</i> <b>please do not send me "wanna rp?"</b> - instead, toss me a few plots you've been craving to start stuff between our muses. I also have plotting calls, & memes. I prefer intensively exploring chemistry between muses, & 'wanna rp?' doesn't really give me very much to work with. </div>
<br />
<div id="left"><img src="https://i.imgur.com/pEMRlHI.png"> <i>important!</i> I unfollow people periodically -- if I do, it's likely because of inactivity (inactive 2+ months), or if you become exclusive with a version of my muse. I very rarely unfollow for any specific reason, but <b>UNTAGGED NSFW, EXCESSIVE GORE, TRANSPHOBIA, NAZISM, PEDOPHILIA, ANTISEMITISM & RACISM</b> are the big ones. I will unfollow & block for the last five.  </div>
<br /><br />

<p><center><h3>blog schedule & general activity&nbsp;&nbsp;</h3></center>
<p>I run several RP blogs & work full time, so sometimes it’s a hot-buttered minute before I can get to things. I am entirely fine with someone coming to me about activity, especially if there’s a chance I might’ve missed a draft, etc, I only ask that it’s respectful. My day to be singularly devoted to the multi’s <b>LONGER THREADS</b> & in-depth interactions are <i>FRIDAYS</i>. I currently run all of my blogs on a queue to keep activity consistent as well as to take the pressure off myself & my partners for timely replies. 

<p>when I'm not on the dash, you can find me through my <a href="https://mangohub.tumblr.com/">rp hub</a>, or on discord.
<br /><br />

<p><center><h3>shipping (romantic & platonic)&nbsp;&nbsp;</h3></center>
<p><b>ROMANTIC:</b> I ship <i>chemistry</i>. I write Clary as biromantic, bisexual, but still require a fairly significant amount of plotting to establish relationships.

<p><b>PLATONIC:</b>  I am more than excited to explore familial & platonic relationships with all of my muses. This blog is also <b>familial OC friendly</b>, I just ask that we plot things first so I have an idea of how they may fit into my different divergences, or interactions with my muse.

<p>some canon/canon involved ships you may see on this blog include <b>clace, climon</b>, & <b>clizzy</b>.
<br /><br />


<p><center><h3>mains & exclusives&nbsp;&nbsp;</h3></center>
<p><b>EXCLUSIVES:</b> these are the only interpretation of a portrayal I will interact with currently. I am comfortable with this given a history of extensive communication, well developed & fleshed out plots, & a solid relationship with the muns. 

<p><b>MAINS:</b> these are the muses muses i will go to first when it comes to plots & threads, but am NOT exclusive with.

<p>You can find the specifics of these two categories <b>per muse</b> on their extended information popups, as well as <b>pan-blog exclusivity</b> on the accompanying tab on this page.

<div id="left"><img src="https://i.imgur.com/pEMRlHI.png"> <i>important!</i> all exclusives have ooc communication as a cornerstone. I recognize that life becomes busy as hell - however, if we go a month or more without <b>ANY FORM OF INTERACTION IC OR OOC</b>, i reserve the right to remove someone from the list & open the spot up to another so we can both explore new dynamics.  </div>
<br /><br />

