     <li style="width:100px">navigation</li>
</ul>  
</div>

<ul id="tab">
<li class="active">
<h4>why a schedule</h4>
<br />
<p>After mantaining (or trying to maintain) various blog on this blue hellsite for far too long, I've come to realize that the only way I can evenly distribute activity between all of my blogs, as well as keep myself from becoming too overwhelmed by some of them, is by implementing a schedule. this schedule is <b>set but flexible</b>. you can find it outlined on the following tab. 

<p>generally speaking, on the day listed, that blog will have <b>priority</b>. I'll login there first, tackle whatever tracked threads, drafts, or inbox thngs are there, then I'm free to meander through the dash as I like. if there isn't much to do on that blog, I'll scoot over to another who might be a little behind, or who has extra projects. or I may just pop over wherever I'm feeling. 

<p>this doesn't mean that that day is the only day I'll be on the blog! it just means that on that day, there's <b>a specific starting point</b> before I wander elsewhere. it keeps me accountable ;)
<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
</li>

<li>
<h4>blog schedule</h4>
