<ul id="poptab">
<li class="active">
<h4>description</h4>

<p>It wasn't an alliance anyone saw coming. Valentine wasn't dead - Jocelyn believed this deep in her bones, even after having seen the smoldering remains of the Fairchild mansion. He had prepared for this <i>too well</i>, & Jocelyn knew it was only a matter of time before he found her again. After fleeing Idris, Jocelyn fled first to Paris, & then to New York. Nowhere she went seemed far enough away, & when Clary was six, Jocelyn took her to Magnus Bane in the hopes that he could somehow close her inner eye to the Shadow World. Magnus had another idea, entirely.

<p>An old friend visiting the warlock happened to overhear the exchange, & offered an alternate - less damaging - solution. Nephilim blood was distateful to vampires, after all, & she could smell the elevated levels in the girl. Sonja offered to take her, & raise her far away from anywhere Valentine would even think to look for her. The vampire clan wasn't especially friendly to the likes of him - especially not a clan lead by a <b>FORMER NEPHILIM</b>. 

<p>Jocelyn agreed - anything to keep her daughter out of the hands of the man who had defiled her son & killed her own parents - & Clary was taken to <b>Ördögház</b> to be raised among the clan. There, she would train among the vampires & their special forces - the Death Dealers - so that one day she could re0enter the shadow world & stand a fighty chance. 

<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
<br>
<br>
</li>

