<li>
<h4>headcanons</h4>
<p>- Clary has a unique set of abilities gained from her <b>nephilim blood</b>, which is further enhanced because of her connection to the angel <b>ithuriel</b>. She can draw <a href="https://shadowhunters.fandom.com/wiki/Runes">runes on her skin</a>, & those runes give her special abilities dependent on what she draws. She's the only one of her people who can create new runes. 

<p>- Because of her ambiguously human status, she works for <b>SHIELD</b> as a top level agent but largely assists <b>STRIKE</b> & the Avengers. 

<p>- She does & will not use guns. Instead, she relies on the two special black adamas swords she's carried with her since before falling through to this timeline. 

<p>- in this verse, she lives in a row house in Manhttan that, in her home timeline, had been <a href="https://shadowhunters.fandom.com/wiki/Garroway_Books">Garroway Books</a>, a bookstore owned by her step-father, Luke Garroway. It was purchased for her by the engineerings of her lawyer, Darcy Lewis (<a href="http://darcywho.tumblr.com/">@darcywho</a>).

<h1>carried over from her centurion verse</h1>

<blockquote>
    <p>- my interpretation of the <b>scholomance & centurions</b> comes largely from personal headcanon & the wiki for the time being.

<p>- the centurions have a medallion or pin that signifies their status; the pin has a pattern of a leafless stick and the words primi ordines on it. they also have their family crests on the back of their gear. 
    
<p>- she has several runes unique to her as a Centurion, given her connection to Ithuriel: a nameless combination rune across her right peck, over her heart, that invokes the phrases <b>AVE ATQUE VALE</b> (hail & farewell) & <b>PULVIS ET UMBRA SUMUS</b> (we are dust and shadows) - the traditional words said over the dead. this rune signifies her status as a <b>CENTURION</b>, acknowledging that she will die alone with no one to say the words over her body, & that she has already accepted death while still living.
    
<p>- in this verse, she has & carries both <b>Phaesphoros</b> & <b>Heosphoros</b>. 
    <blockquote>
        <p><b>heosphoros:</b> the length of a forearm - half the size of Phaesphoros. Made of black gold & adamas. The cross-guard, grip, & pommel are gold with obsidian, & the blade is a silver so dark that it looks nearly black. On the other side of the blade, along the center ridge, is a pattern of black stars, symbolizing the Morgensterns. Kept in a dark leather scabbard with a pattern of silver stars sewn through it
        
        <p><b>phaesphoros:</b> Of the same design as its sister blade, but nearly twice the size. 
    </blockquote>
    
<p>- The rune she drew on Jace <i>did</i> work, just not in the way she thought. Instead of bringing Jace back, it tied their souls together, enabling her to absorb some of the same abilities he had possessed to to his own connection to Ithuriel. This is what enabled her to advance so rapidly in training after his death, even if she doesn't know it.
</blockquote>
 
<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
