<ul id="poptab">
<li class="active">
<h4>description</h4>
<p>Unlike many students at Hogwarts, Clary was plucked from her mundane middle school in sixth grade, having spent much of her childhood largely ensconced in the quiet but creative life her mother had carved for her & her brother in a flat in Brooklyn after fleeing her abusive marriage. She has no memory of her father, & had Jocelyn had it her way, they would have remained normal children growing up safe & unattached to the world their father & his followers had corrupted for her.

<p>Unfortunately, it wouldn’t last; Clary was nine years old when her older brother, Jonathan, received a strange letter in the mail, stamped with a wax crest, & written in glittering ink. The next thing she knew, she was hand in hand with her mother, brother scowling on the other side, as Jocelyn took the wand she had hidden for eleven years & accompanied her son to Diagon Alley for the list of things he would need to start school. 

<p>It was there, tucked away in a small corner in the back of Flourish & Blotts, that both children found books that would go on to influence their school career for years to come. For Clary, it was a hand-illustrated copy of Winogrand's Wondrous Water Plants<sup>1</sup>. The pictures inspired her own art, & she began studying & drawing these new, fantastic plants even before she started her own first year at Hogwarts two years later.

<p>Over the next few years, she’d continue to read up on the world she had become aware of even while attending school in the muggle world. She excelled at art, often using her whimsical drawings inspired by herbology textbooks for school illustrations. She also found science fascinating, gravitating to biology & botany on a small scale during labs. It was during this time she also discovered Beatrix Potter & her own work as a scientific illustrator<sup>2</sup>.

<p>It was also during this time, however, that Valentine reappeared, kidnapping Jonathan while he was in transit between the school & their home over Christmas break. Clary would remember that as the defining moment that changed her brother, turning him into someone far more quiet, & determined, than he had been before.

<p>When she turned 11, her own letter came & she accompanied Jocelyn to Diagon Alley alongside her brother, only this time she was the one to come home with a wand, a cauldron, & a Tawny Owl of her own that she named Beatrix<sup>3</sup>. She was later sorted into Gryffindor, hardly a surprise given it was her mother’s house, & putting her slightly & humorously in contrast to her brother, who had been placed in Slytherin five years earlier. 

<p>Like her earlier muggle schooling, Clary was surprised to discover much of it had carried over - she excelled at herbology, as well as charm work. While Potions didn’t quite come naturally to her, her brother’s tutelage helped immensely & she developed an affinity for them in her own way. 

<p>She would later receive OWLs that advanced her interests in Herbology & Charms, as well as various other subjects, then also received  high or at least passing grades in the following subjects for her NEWTs: Charms, Defense Against the Dark Arts, Herbology, Transfiguration, Arithmancy, Ancient Runes & Potions.  

<p><center><h3>notes</h3></center>

<p><sup>1</sup>written & illustrated in the same style as Beatrix Potters’ works

<p><sup>2</sup>had she not eventually gone to Hogwarts, Clary likely would have followed a similar career path to her inspiration & gone into scientific illustration & botany based research.

<p><sup>3</sup>named after her inspiration, naturally.

<p>- verse is compliant with my own <a href="https://affcgato.tumblr.com/">Jonathan’s</a> Hogwarts Professor verse, but can happily be alternately plotted to accommodate others’ canons.

