<h4>notes on interaction</h4>

<p><b2>option i</b2>. hogwarts, as faculty.	
<blockquote>
<p>as a professor at hogwarts, Clary lives & works on the school grounds. she can typically be found in the greenhouses, or in her office. she can also typically be found sketching by the lake, weather permitting.
</blockquote>

<p><b2>option ii</b2>. diagon alley.
<blockquote>
    <p>infrequently, clary makes trips to diagon alley for anything she can procure from dogweed & deathcap or grow herself in the greenhouses. she tries to schedule those trips so she can meet up with friends or family, but she always leaves a bit of free time so she can explore new shops or have some time to herself so she won't feel rushed.
</blockquote>

<p><b2>option iii</b2>. hogsmede.	
<blockquote>
    <p>clary tends to disappear to the village on weekends, helping residents with little projects & spending time helping with inventory & ordering for Dogweed and Deathcap, or meeting with friends at Three Broomsticks.
</blockquote>


<p><b2>option iv</b2>. abroad.
<blockquote>
    <p>sometimes Clary is called to other schools to teach niche herbology matters, or to help cultivate rare & delicate pieces that others struggle with. there's always a chance for her to encounter another muse while doing so!
</blockquote>

<p><b2>option v</b2>. prior to Hogwarts.
<blockquote>
    <p>Clary initially attended a muggle school in Brooklyn, prior to being sent her letter. It's definitely an option, however she's been largely removed from that world since her brother got his letter a year before her & left for Hogwarts.
option vi. hogwarts, as a student.
</blockquote>
  
