<li>
<p><h4>variants</h4>

<p><b>arc i</b>; <i>empress</i>.

<blockquote>
    ( <b>single ship  variant</b> with <a href="https://bastxrds.tumblr.com">@bastxrds</a>. ) in this arc, Clary became empress alongside Emperor Hux after tearing apart all of those who would have seen her tethered to a workbench for the rest of her life, making weapons for one side or another in the ongoing war. now she acts as his chief diplomat, building their empire while staying at his side as his enduring wife. 
</blockquote>

<br>

    <p><b>arc ii</b>; <i>original trilogy</i>. 
    
    <blockquote>
    coming soon, centered around the events of <b>rogue one</b>. After her tenure as handmaiden to <b>queen amidala</b> on Naboo, Clary has transitioned to her post-handmaiden life by working with <b>Galen Erso</b>, working in the field of crystallography & studying the energy potential for synthetic & natural kybers.
    
    <p><b>tag:</b> ☆ ❛ science doesn't take sides ❜ || arc ii. ( original )<br>
    <b>note:</b> this is the only arc where Clary will actively carry a lightsaber - hers is a <b>dual-phase</b> lightsaber, utilizing two different kybers she's honed in her time. she's proficient in form i, having trained at the jedi temple on coruscant as a necessity after her gifts became apparent, but she is not a jedi, nor does she have extensive formal training - merely enough for self defense. 
    
    <p>the primary kyber she utilizes is a <b>ghostfire</b> crystal, producing a nearly translucent blade that leaves an afterimage capable of distorting oppenents. the second is a <b>blackwing</b> crystal, as a callback to her time on <i>dathomir</i>. 
    
    <p>additionally, in this verse - similar to it's prequel verse - her focus has been on academic pursuit instead of manual crafting & force transference, so she's more combat inclined than she is invested in her work as a weapons engineer.
</blockquote>

<br>

    <p><b>arc iii</b>; <i>prequel trilogy</i>. 
    <blockquote>
    coming soon. serving as a handmaiden to then-<b>Queen Amidala</b>, Clary's innate diathim abilities assisted her queen in unique ways, enabling her to better protect her queen alongside the other handmaidens - something she would continue to do long after the young monarch had left Naboo to take up her role as senator in the Galactic Senate. 
    
    <p><b>tag:</b>☆ ❛ as timeless as infinity ❜ || arc iii. ( prequels )<br>
    <b>note:</b> additionally, in this verse - similar to its follow verse set surrounding the original trilogy - her focus has been on academic pursuit instead of manual crafting & force transference, so she's more combat inclined than she is invested in her work as a weapons engineer.

</blockquote>

