<li>
<h4>interaction ideas</h4>
<p><b>option i.</b> meeting during her younger years. 
<blockquote>
    <p>almost from birth until roughly five years before the events of The Force Awakens, Jocelyn & Clary were constantly on the move, weaving in & out of the unknown regions, as well as vaulting into wild space, all in the effort to stay one step ahead of Valentine, the cold war Imperial remnant, or anyone else who might seek to abuse Clary’s abilities for themselves.
</blockquote>
    
<p><b>option ii.</b> meeting through the Resistance. 
<blockquote>
    <p>With the public formation of the First Order in 29 ABY, it became even harder to hide in the shadows so Jocelyn turned to some of her oldest connections. The help came too late for Jocelyn, who was captured & returned to her husband’s side, but Clary was able to get away & has been with the Resistance since. 
</blockquote>
    
<p><b>option iii.</b> meeting through captivity. 
<blockquote>
    <p>Prior to the events of The Force Awakens, it’s highly probable that Clary would have fallen into the First Order’s hands, & as such would function as a very valuable hostage. While in captivity, she's held on the <b>finalizer</b>, constrained largely to her workshop that's not entirely far from the sick bay. 
</blockquote>

<p><b>arc specific interaction</b>; <i>empress</i>. ( <b>single ship  variant</b>. ) this arc is also open to interaction on a by request basis!
 
