<li>
<h4>headcanons</h4>

<p>- given naboos tradition of secrecy surrounding the monarcy, she was able to detatch herself from her royal persona, ruling under the name <b2>Queen Édel</b2> from 20 ABY to 22 ABY, when she was twelve until age sixteen, when she feld the planet with her mother in the dead of night after the official transfer of power but before her father could sink his claws in.

<p>- <b>Regarding her parents</b>, <i>Jocelyn Fairchild</i> is the daughter of one of the Naboo Royal Handmaidens, & <i>Valentine Morgenstern</i> is a Diathim from Millius Prime.
            
<p>her unique genetic makeup, coupled with the environment Jocelyn was exposed to after fleeing Valentine & escaping into <b>wild space</b> while pregnant with her daughter lead to her unique abilities.
            
<p> while she's only <b>half diathim</b>, she does retain some of the abilities of her father's people - namely an unusually graceful gait that could almost be described as gliding, a resistance ( but, unlike a full Diathim, not total immunity ) to the effects of exposure to the vacuum of interplanetary space without the assistance of a protective suit or life support, & some degree of their natural hypnotic abilities that manifest namely in her ability to <b>somewhat</b> influence & de-escalate conflicting tempers before things spiral out of hand.
        
<p> Her workshop is hidden largely due to the high population of imported <a href="https://starwars.fandom.com/wiki/Ysalamir">ysalamiri</a>, most known for their ability to repel the Force by creating a Force-neutral bubble. It's a flimsy precaution, but so far that plus the intense secrecy surrounding her location have done wonders to keep her off others' radar.          

<p><center><h3>skills & abilities</h3></center>

<p>officially, Clary is a <b>crystallographer</b> with an emphasis on energy transference & enhancement, much like Galen Erso. It was much of his research, coupled with her training under <a href="https://bastxrds.tumblr.com/">Yennefer of Dathomir</a>, that lead to her contorl & abilities that would later make her a target of the First Order & its shadow parasite, the Final Order itself. What makes her unique is she can do work at a far, far faster pace & on a greater scale without needing significant machination - something a regular human typically cannot do, but she can thanks to her Force abilities.

<p>other skills include, but aren't limited to; 

<blockquote>
    <p>some amount of ability to <b>shield her thoughts</b>
    <p>force trance - only to be used under the most dire circumstances while transporting her but with some speculation she may be capable of morichro 
    <p>perhaps most dubiously, her ability to sever force connections.
</blockquote> 

<p><b>important!</b> anything outside of her normal range of transference takes a significantly harder toll on her body & means significant time to recover. 
 
<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />

</li>
<li>
<p><h4>plotted dynamics</h4>

<p><div id="exclusives"><div id="left"><img src="https://i.imgur.com/hOYh8MV.png"></div> <b>Armitage Hux</b>, <a href="https://bastxrds.tumblr.com">@bastxrds</a>. She was never supposed to end up on this side of the war. After the transfer of power on Naboo, she had packed what few precious belongings she had & fled the planet for Dathomir. She was supposed to be <b>safe</b>, but eventually she had to leave the only other planet she's ever called home. After spending years hiding in Wild Space, she was picked up by First Order operatives & brought aboard the Finalizer.
<p>She never expected to fall in with the other - he was merely someone who checked her work, who kept an eye on her so that she wouldn't fall behind, but somehow the two of them developed a deeper bond as they navigated the complexities of the First Order, & when they learned of Palpatine's return, & how the First Order was to be fodder for the Sith Cultists' amibition. When the Final Order turned their guns & ships against the First Order, it was the two of them who ensured the right side walked away.
<p>Now, residing on <b>Drommund Kaas</b>, Clary sits as the trusted diplomat to the new emperor in the eyes of the public. In private, things are a little more complicated.
</div>    

<p><div id="exclusives"><div id="left"><img src="https://i.imgur.com/CIRfkjH.png"></div> <b>Rey Dameron</b>, <a href="https://griserey.tumblr.com">@griserey</a>. She's too little to be alone. It's what Clary had thought wen she first laid eyes on the girl, not that much younger than her, when they had been forced to make an emergency landing on Jakku after an unofficial visit into the wilds of the Unknown Regions. Clary shouldn't have exited the shuttle, but when one of her handmaidens reported a curiously young girl, the Queen hadn't thought twice. 

<p>Bringing Rey back with them after that had been almost a given, & Clary had delayed their depature to allow the girl to collect her meager possessions before bringing her back to Naboo. Now the two are inseparable, & Clary couldn't be more glad for her very well-trained shadow.
</div>   

<p><div id="exclusives"><div id="left"><img src="https://i.imgur.com/i4FKEGy.jpg"></div> <b>Jace Herondale</b>, <a href="https://ofangelicblood.tumblr.com">@ofangelicblood</a>. She's had other pilots - lots of them, really. a veritable string of endless faces that have ferried her from moon to moon, from planet to planet to planet. it comes with the territory of keeping a low profile & staying off the first order's radar she she's forgotten more faces than most have met over the years. none of have them have ever let her sit up front before, though. in fact, none of them have acknowledged their all too human cargo is anything but cargo, so faced with a surely pilot who doesn't mind letting her have a view, it'sa bit of a surprise.
</div>   

<p><div id="exclusives"><div id="left"><img src="https://i.imgur.com/qdrDLjM.png"></div> <b>Crimson</b>, <a href="https://onehell-of-apilot.tumblr.com">@onehell-of-apilot</a>. She always knew the First Order would find her, it was only a matter of time. Hiding away on a remote moon in the Outer Rim with only her favorite ysalamiri for company, she's enjoyed a quiet few years of living in a gilded cage but after a shady run in during a supply run, she knew her days were numbered. when they sent the best pilot to pick her up, she knew better than to fight it.
<p>what's interesting is the realization that he belongs there even less than she does, & the feelings that come with that realization. 
</div>    

