<ul id="poptab">
<li class="active">
<h4>description</h4>
<p><b>SSA CLARISSA FAIRCHILD</b>. after a lucrative decade of working as a high class art forger, Clary was tracked & brought in by agents of the Behavioral Analysis Unit as an added bonus while tracking a series of document forgeries she had done for <b>the circle</b>. recognizing her unique talent, she was offered a deal similar to one offered to one Penelope Garcia years prior, & now she works for the BAU as an agent & experience profiler.

<p>it wasn’t a life she had wanted for herself, but it was one her father had envisioned when he had seen her unique ability to take a work of art, see it once, & replicate it with near perfection. after years of honing that skill & having her practice for hours on end, Clary was raised to become an expert in forging not only <i>rare works of art</i>, but also <b>documents</b> & other things necessary for her father & his group - The Circle - to keep functioning. she was kept away from the other facets of the group’s operation - the trafficking of bodies, narcotics, small arms - but working in her studio until her fingers bled, she kept all of it running for several years until time ran out.

<p>she was grateful when they found her because it meant things might finally end. she’d given up on the hope of anything resembling a <b>NORMAL LIFE</b>, but finding out her father had lied to her all these years, that she had a mother, a brother, & even a nephew waiting for her out there that her father had told her were all dead is what had her accept the deal to take her skills & apply them in a way she might help rather than hurt. she finished her training in record time, & advanced through the academy like no one had seen in a good, long time, taking her place on the team amid some healthy skepticism.

<p>now she works <b>FOR THE OTHER SIDE</b>. officially she’s part of the elite art theft rapid deployment team - a group of twenty agents based in Washington D.C. each responsible for addressing art and cultural property crime cases in an assigned geographic region, but unofficially she partners with the BAU in Quantico more often than not, tracking <b>THE CIRCLE</b> so that the activities of one of the most notorious international criminal groups might finally grind to a halt.

