<ul id="poptab">
<li class="active">
<h4>description</h4>

<p>The lavish & competitive world of Regency London high society with its intricate rules & dramatic but subtle power struggles. At the heart of this world, high society families compete for royal favors, & to ensure their legacies - often in the form of high class marriages. After the death of the contentious <b>Lord Morgenstern</b> under tantalizingly mysterious circumstances, Clarissa & her older brother were finally ready to shed their mourning colors & re-enter society - just in time for Clarissa to make her <b>debut</b> for the season. 

<p>After being presented to the Queen, Clary was singled out as one of the most eligible young women of the season - & a good thing, too, as it will take an incomparable match to secure her place after her father's rumored dabblings in black magic & the occult.</p>

<p>things were going fine, & she even caught the eye of the young Lord Herondale, though there were some whisperings of a scandal in the attention her brother also paid the young man. all of it seemed to die down, & their wedding & the subsequent ball they threw at the end of the season was something incomparable but the ton was still quite glad when the young couple decided to take <b>A YEAR ABROAD</b> following their marriage. no one could have expected what would happen next.</p>

<p>a widow within the first year of her wedding, Clary returned to London to take over the Herondale estates with the failing health of the family’s aging matriarch & act as guardian to the two sole heirs of the Herondale & Morgenstern lines until they might come of age. she wears the mourning colors <b>LIKE ARMOR</b>, & she’s skeptical of the motives of anyone & everyone who comes near her family - well-intentioned or not.&nbsp;</p>

<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
<br>
<br>
</li>

<li>
<h4>interaction ideas</h4>
<p><b>option i</b>, meeting in a public place. 
<blockquote>
    <p>though heavily private after the passing of her husband, Clary makes a point to enjoy the small things in life. as such, she might be found at the opera or the theatre during the week.
</blockquote>

<p><b>option ii</b>, meeting at an event during the season.
<blockquote>
    <p>as is custom, it wouldn't be unusual for Clary to attend 1-2 balls a week during <a title="a six-month period between about November & July when the aristocrats would descend upon London from their country estates in order to secure their status by working their contacts, forming allegiances, buying & selling property.">the season</a>, though she's more likely to err on the side of fewer given her charges & responsibilities. she also might make an appearance at one of the weekly evening parties thrown by a hostess, but it's heavily unlikely she would throw one for herself given her younger charges & her attentiveness to them. these parties mostly ended every night in London between 2 & 4 a.m., except Sundays.
    <p>she might be tempted to throw one later in the spring, though, or as a party for one of her boys.
</blockquote>

<p><b>option iii</b>, introduction through friends.
<blockquote>
    <p>after a formal introduction through friends in passing at a party or event, Clary is open to receiving visitors during morning calls but as she's somewhat removed from societal happenings, this is more true in theory than practice & calling on her might cause a flurry of activity to get something ready. 
</blockquote>

<p><b>option iv</b>, meeting during promenade.
<blockquote>
    <p>As it was essential to be seen at Hyde Park during the promenade hour of 5.00 to 6.00 pm, Clary might sometimes be seen there with her boys, or with a trusted friend if only to keep current with the goings on around her. 
</blockquote>


