<li>
<h4>headcanons</h4>

<p>- for non-old guard muses / those looking for a purely period au, please feel free to disregard all tog centric headcanons!
for old guard muses, the same (time period relevant/pervasive) headcanons from her main tog verse apply!

<p>- clary is guardian to both kit & ash in this verse, & many of her decisions are based on caring for them & looking after their needs until such time as they can formally accept their titles & look after their lands. the two boys spend the majority of time with their governesses, but clary is a very active participant in their lives. 

<p>- kit is significantly older than ash, & is nearly ready to take on his adult responsibilities which gives clary a bit of freedom in knowing that the herondale line is secure. in return, kit is comfortable in supporting her because of her connection to his distant cousin. this enables her to keep her freedom without being forced to remarry upon her mourning year’s completion. 

<p>- as a widow, clary enjoys a bit more freedom than her unmarried counterparts might enjoy, leaving her free to conduct her affairs discretely. 

<p>- her official title is <b2>duchess herondale</b2>, stylized as her grace. she’ll become the dowager duchess herondale once kit officially marries & becomes duke herondale officially. 

<p>- clary stays in <b>half mourning</b>, which is marked by grey or lilac coloring, even thought the year mark has come & gone. she does this to note she's not particularly interested in re-entering society to find another match.

<p>- Clary takes breakfast (& usually lunch) with both Kit & Ash every morning, no matter how busy they all are.

<p>- both boys are seen to by a different governess, to accommodate their significant age difference. additionally, Kit has various tutors in a wide range of subjects & Ash will be expected to have the same as he grows older.

<p>- during the london season, she & the boys reside at Hanover Terrace, which overlooks Regent's Park, London. It was built two years prior to the 1813 season by reknown architect John Nash. It is situated on the west side of Regents Park offering a wide range of recreational facilities including London Zoo, & the wide-open green spaces of Regents Park itself.

