<ul id="poptab">
<li class="active">
<h4>description</h4>
<p>once the guardian of <i2>Tyche</i2>, Clary was the guardian of fortune & prosperity before the destruction of the original silver millennium. the oldest of the senshi, Clary was <i>heir apparent</i> before the birth of princess serenity. this is because her mother was eos, sister to selene.

<p>when the silver millennium fell, Clary died alongside the other guardians & was reborn because of the actions of Queen Serenity on 20<sup>th</sup> century earth. while the other scouts were reborn close to each other, the destruction of Tyche before she could be reborn meant Clary was set adrift. 

<p>being born in Manhattan, Clary grew up a long, long way away from the rest of the senshi. in a way, this was fitting given her status as the <b>spare</b> in case something should happen to Usagi - while she can no longer transform, she can still wield the <i2>silver crystal</i2>. 
<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
</li>

<li>
<h4>interaction ideas</h4>
<p><b>option i</b>, <i>meeting in a public place</i>. 

<p><b>option ii</b>, <i>meeting in a previous lifetime</i>. 
<br />
<br />
<br />
</li>

<li>
<h4>headcanons</h4>
<p>- because of her original status as <i>heir apparent</i> prior to Serenity's birth, or the event Serenity & Endymion fail to produce an heir, Clary has the crescent mark on her forehead marking her as part of the moon kingdom's royal family. 

<p>- this verse is influenced by the same <b>greek lore</b> surrounding Queen Serenity as the manifestation of <i>Selene</i>.

<p>- her colors are lilac & olive green. 

<br />
<br />
<br />

</li>
    
</div>


<div id="f09" class="popup_block">
<div id="popside">

<div id="popsideimage"><img src="https://i.imgur.com/pCBqFcK.png"></div> <!-- change the image on the popup sidebar -->

<ul id="poptabs">
     <li class="active" style="width:100px">description</li>
		
     <li style="width:100px">interaction options</li>
     
     <li style="width:100px">headcanons</li>
     
</ul>  

</div> 

<ul id="poptab">
<li class="active">
<h4>description</h4>
<blockquote>
    <p>this verse uses Clary's <b>canon variant</b> <i>centurion</i> verse as backstory. for details, you can find that verse under the variant's tab under <b>evening star (alt.) centurion</b>, but no knowledge of her canon is required as any muse she interacts with in this verse would likely be aware of the dimension she comes from.
</blockquote>

<p><b>2007</b>, the battle of the burren. given the sword <b>glorious</b>, Clary & her friends believed this sword would end the second in a series of wars initially waged by her father, but kept alight by the brother she never knew she had. all she had to do was stab her soulmate with the sword, & it would sever the connection between him, & Jonathan. that's what they believed, anyway.

<p><b>it didn't work.</b> instead of severing the connection, Jace & Jonathan both were killed instantly. It ended the war, but drove a wedge between Clary & the rest of the survivors. When she eventually chose to leave & be trained as a Centurion, she opted not to look back. 

<p>finishing training was brutal, but taking up the mantle of a centurion meant the assurance no one could ever get the best of her again. as the Clave's emissary for the more <i>difficult</i> missions, Clary would go on to make a name for herself-- one that would have significant consequences.

<p>ten years after the battle of the burren, Clary would take a mission that ended with a face to face confrontation with Lilith. that would be the last time anyone heard from her - unbeknownst to anyone, Lilith had waited until the perfect moment to strike her revenge. Ripping open a portal, Lilith hurled her through it into an alternate dimension - one without Shadowhunters, Raziel, or the mortal instruments. 

<p>waking up in a New York City that was foreign to her & finding everyone <b>gone</b>, Clary knows that she has to <b>find lilith</b> in <i>this</i> dimension if she ever wants to think of finding her way home. it's a good thing her unique skills still work though - while this world might not know Shadowhunters, demons are still plenty active. Teaming up with hunters means she has access to information, & ammo.

<p>Eventually, that info is going to help her get home. At least, that's her hope -- if the place she calls home even still exists. 
<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
</li>

<li>
<h4>interaction ideas</h4>
<p><b>option i</b>, <i>meeting in a public place</i>. 
<br />
<br />
<br />
