<ul id="poptab">
<li class="active">
<h4>description</h4>
<p>The newest addition to the foodie group, Clary has watched her older brother, <b>jonathan</b>, & his success with his restaurant - <i>per se</i>. While Clary has always been more of a baker than a cook, that didn't stop Jonathan from pushing his sister to try new things. Opening her bakery, <i>the cooling rack</i>, was the culmination of many, many years of experimentation & tough love. 

<p>She sources her spices from <a href="http://affcgato.tumblr.com/">Magnus</a>' <b>saffron</b>, & hand-delivers a selection of tea cakes & biscuits to <a href="http://bastxrds.tumblr.com/">Tessa</a>'s <b>infused</b> daily. in fact, it was at <b>infused</b> that she found her partner in crime; <a href="http://bastxrds.tumblr.com/">lucie herondale</a>. 
<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
</li>

<li>
<h4>notes</h4>
<p>the schedule for the bakery is as followers:
        <b><center>daily offerings:</center></b>
    <blockquote>
        <p>- vegan Banana Bread
        <p>- Blue Ridge Mountain Herb
        <p>- Cinnamon Raisin Walnut
        <p>- Cinnamon Swirl
        <p>- Dinner Rolls (6-pack) ( Choose from: Honey Wheat / Hearty White / Sunflower Whole Wheat / Multi-Grain / Challah / Cinnamon Raisin Walnut / Blue Ridge Mountain Herb )
            <p>- English Muffin Bread
        <p>- Garlic Knots (6-pack) ( Fresh Garlic / Butter / Minced Onions / Sesame / Poppy )
        <p>- Hearty White
        <p>- Honey Whole Wheat
        <p>- Old Fashioned White
        <p>- Pumpkin Bread
        <p>- Spelt Bread
        <p>- Sunflower
    </blockquote>
        <b><center>weekly offerings:</center></b>
        <blockquote>
    <p>- <b>Monday:</b> ( <i>available for pickup, only</i> ) Cherry Apple Challah
    <p>- <b>Tuesday:</b> Ukrainian Black
    <p>- <b>Wednesday:</b> Blue-fruity bread*
    <p>- <b>Thursday:</b> Blue-Fruity Bread*
    <p>- <b>Friday:</b> Kosher Challah, Cherry Apple Challah
    <p>- <b>Saturday:</b> Baker's choice / baker's experiment of the week.
    <p>- <b>Sunday:</b> Cheddar Garlic ( <i>available for pickup, only</i> )
        </blockquote>
    
<p>* Blue-Fruity Bread will be one or more of the following: Blueberry with Cranberry, Pineapple, Mango, Apricot or Papaya.    

<p>a few specialties of the bakery are;

<blockquote>
    <p>- <a href="https://www.hanielas.com/christmas-poinsettia-meringues/">christmas poinsettia meringues</a>
    <p>- <a href="https://www.gimmesomeoven.com/coconut-lime-shortbread-cookies/">coconut lime shortbread cookies</a>
    <p>- homemade <b>marshmallows</b> that she sells by the pre-weighed package with seasonal offerings on rotation
    <p>- lots & lots of <b>handpies</b>, including strawberry rhubarb, white peach + rose + basil,  & sweet potato + chorizo. 
    <p>- rotating selection of loaves, to include
        <blockquote>
            <p>- challah, on fridays
            <p>- baguettes, sourdough, multigrain offered <b>daily</b>.
        </blockquote>
    <p>- croissants - classic, & chocolate + sea salt
    <p>- scones - apricot-rosemary is the bakery's signature sweet, & <b>Caramelized Onion, Gruyere, Chive</b> is the signature savory.
    <p>- seasonal selection of <b>swiss rolls</b>, including yule logs.
</blockquote>

<p>a few things she has sourced to <b>infused</b> include

<blockquote>
    <p>- Chocolate Tarts with White Chocolate Mousse filling topped with sprinkle hearts, strawberries & raspberries
    <p>- lemon tea cookies
    <p>- historically accurate <b>candied ginger</b>
    <p>- historically accurate Elizabethan <b>honeycakes</b>
</blockquote>
<br />
<br />
</li>

<li>
<h4>headcanons</h4>
<p>she keeps <b>dark chocolate dipped figs with sea salt</b> on hand for Kate as a fun alternative to chocolate covered strawberries. 

<p>a personal favorite but very challenging thing she's made was a custom order - a vegan <b>Rose Cardamom & Blood Orange Loaf Cake</b>, ordered by Andrew as a birthday cake for Kate. 

<p>she semi-regularly makes <b>baklava</b> for Andy. 
