<ul id="poptab">
<li class="active">
<h4>description</h4>

<p>there are a lot of words for what <b>valentine morgenstern</b> was, but the one absolutely certain thing is that he was effective. While other kids did girl scouts or soccer, Clary & her brother attended wilderness survival workshops, hunting parties, & learned everything to prepare them for the war he kept promising was coming. 

<p>his uprising & the prophecied separation never materialized, for better or worse, & Jocelyn managed to flee with her children while Valentine was too busy arranging yet another wilderness survey just before Clary's sixteenth birthday. With her mother settled in Brooklyn, Clary working her way through school, & Jonathan throwing himself into the culinary world, it would seem that the three Fairchilds could finally start to adjust to something vaguely resembling a normal life.

<p>while she had always loved art growing up, there was a part of her that couldn't shake her father's words entirely. & that's what inevitably lead her to apply for a graduate program in medical illustration at Johns Hopkins University School of Medicine. 

<p>After too many years away at school, Clary moved back to Manhattan to be close to her remaining family. Everything would have been great, if the world hadn't decided that was the perfect time for everything to go right to hell. ... just like her father had told her it would.

<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
</li>

<li>
<h4>options</h4>

<p><b2>option i</b2>. as an isolated survivor in the city.

<blockquote>
    <p>Clary spends much of her day scavenging for supplies, so it's heavily possible that someone could run into her while she's pilfering medicine, toilet paper, or food. alternately, she can also be found in the abandoned halls of the Met.
</blockquote>

<p><b2>option ii</b2>. when it all goes down.	
<blockquote>
    <p>As someone living in the city, there's a variety of ways they could meet as things go down - coming to & from work on public transportation, at an event during the news broadcast, or during an attempted evacuation.
</blockquote>

<p><b2>option iii</b2>. at the compound.	
<blockquote>
    <p>if your muse is traveling during the event, it's always possibly they could come across the compound clary & other survivors have holed up in & make a case for asylum.
</blockquote>

<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
</li>

<li>
<h4>headcanons</h4>

<p>Clary holds a bachelors in design for sustainability with a minor in Scientific Illustration (focus: botany) from Savannah College of Art and Design, & a masters in medical illustration from Johns Hopkins University School of Medicine. 

<p>she additionally has a small library composed of all of the books her illustrations have made it into, making for quite the useful treasure trove of plant identification & medical textbooks.

<p>her home is a <a href="http://onthesetofnewyork.com/iamlegendapartment.html">fortified town house</a> in Greenwich Village - 11 Washington Square Park North. it's been outfitted so that the windows are covered by blackout shades, the door is heavily bolted, & the entire building is soundproof unless you're right on top of it.

<p>alternately, variant where she's part of a band of survivors, she & the other survivors have taken over a factory & adjacent warehouse, outfitting it to be the loudest & brightest building in the city in the hopes that that deters creatures from breaching the perimeter.

<blockquote>
    <p>
in this variant, Clary has the same role but works with other survivors instead of staying isolated in her townhouse - though many of her things are still there, & she occasionally braves the city to go & get them as needed because bringing everything would require more manpower than she can handle alone.
</blockquote>

