<ul id="poptab">
<li class="active">
<h4>description</h4>

<blockquote>
    <p><b>note:</b> I'm comfortable plotting this verse both during & after her time in the Menagerie.
</blockquote>


<p>Originally from the <b2>Wandering Isles</b2>, Clary's mother fled with her after her father's experimentation on her older brother went badly awry & Jocelyn discovered Valentine had started to do the same on her unborn daughter. The would stay on the run for most of Clary's life, fleeing to the <b2>Southern Colonies</b2>in hopes that they may escape his notice. 

<p>They managed for fifteen years before two of her father's associates - <b2>Pangborn</b2> & <b2>Blackwell</b2> - spotted Jocelyn in the market. clary was able to get away, only to be captured by a slave trader. She was pulled aboard, held in irons, & only allowed above deck when they had finally reached Kerch, where she was sold to Tante Heleen's <i>Menagerie</i>.

<p>She spent six months in Heleen's silks before she was able to read her own contract & discovered how much the woman was adding to her own expenses. The realization she would never pay her off made her work harder, testing the limits of the grisha abilities that had manifested in the Colonies, & finding ways to sneak in side jobs. Paying off Heleen should have meant freedom, but instead it was like trading out for a more comfortable cage.

<p>Now she works out of a small attic in the <b2>Zelvar district</b2>, forging documents for a fee & stashing all the money she can get so she might be able to track down her mom, & hoping that she can escape notice of the drüskelle whenever they make berth in Ketterdam's various harbors.

<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
<br>
<br>
<br>
</li>

<li>
<h4>notes</h4>

<p><b>option i.</b> <i>the Menagerie</i>

<blockquote>
    <p>meeting during her time as the mare in Tante Heleen's Menagerie. Clary not only was forced to carry out the terms of her indenture, but found ways to work her odd little side job - selling expert forgeries & small works of her own art to pad her pockets so that she might escape.
</blockquote>

<p><b>option ii.</b> <i>forger</i>

<blockquote>
    <p>meeting in the <b2>zelvar district</b2> after she's escaped Tante Heleen's, & has started working as a forger in Ketterdam while hiding her status as Grisha. She forges documents - writs of transit, permissions for crossings, false itineraries, as well as works of art. 
</blockquote>

<p><b>option iii.</b> <i>variant</i>

<blockquote>
    <p>meeting in a variant of the verse where Clary was taken to the little palace & trained with other Grisha instead of falling into the hands of slavers in the Southern Colonies. 
</blockquote>

<br />
<br />
<br />
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
</li>

<li>
<h4>headcanons</h4>

<p>- because of her father's experimentation on her, Clary's gift as a <b2>Corporalki</b2> tailor is enhanced. She doesn't just hold the ability to manipulate living flesh, but also has an added ability to work as a <b2>fabrikator</b2> in a very limited fashion. It's these complimentary gifts that allow her to expertly forge documents & works of art.

<p>- her favorite food is the small pineapples that are occasionally brought in from the southern colonies, because they remind her of home. sometimes, after she's completed a significant job, she'll buy them candied & hoard the box away in her attic.

<br />
<br />

</li>
<li>
<h4>plotted dynamics</h4>

<p><div id="left"><img src="https://i.imgur.com/QOtNWcC.png"></div>
<b>Kaz Brekker</b></a>, <a href="https://crowgreeds.tumblr.com">@crowgreeds</a> &mdash; after leaving the Menagerie, word of mouth brought the <b2>bastard of the barrel</b2> to her door. it started with a few documents - excellently forged - so that he might move shipments in & out of the harbor, before Dirtyhands discovered her talent for art. Now her best words go to him.


</li>
<li>
<h4>locations</h4>
    
<p><div id="left"><img src="https://i.imgur.com/HHdVBdm.png"></div>
<b>Southern Colonies</b></a> &mdash; located south of Novyi Zem & belonging to Kerch, Clary & her mother called the colonies home for fifteen years after Jocelyn escaped her husband. It was here in one of the markets near a port city whose name she's long since forgotten that Jocelyn was taken by Pangborn & Blackwell, & Clary was hauled onto a Slaver's ship.

<p><div id="left"><img src="https://i.imgur.com/HHdVBdm.png"></div>
<b>The Menagerie</b></a> &mdash; Clary spent six months in Tante Heleen's Menagerie after being forcibly brought to Kerch. She only managed to escape because of her Grisha abilities affording her the ability to take on side work, but those six months (nevermind the time leading up to them, as well) remain some of the most traumatic of her life. She hasn't returned to the West Stave since & refuses work that would mean delivering or walking through that part of Ketterdam. 
    
<p><div id="left"><img src="https://i.imgur.com/HHdVBdm.png"></div>
<b>Zelvar District</b></a> &mdash; after escaping the Menagerie, Clary was lucky to find a small place she could call home in the Zelvar District. It's on the border closest to the East Stave in a run down building that's little more than rickety stairs & warped wood, but the attic is warm enough & she has a small window to see one of the neighboring manse's gardens... as well as most importantly, a door that locks.  
    
<br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br>    
    
</li>    
