<!-- matrix verse -->

<div id="f11" class="popup_block">
<div id="popside">

<div id="popsideimage"><img src="https://i.imgur.com/pCBqFcK.png"></div> <!-- change the image on the popup sidebar -->

<ul id="poptabs">
     <li class="active" style="width:100px">description</li>
     
     <li style="width:100px">interaction options</li>
     
     <li style="width:100px">headcanons</li>
     
     <li style="width:100px">plotted dynamics</li>
     
     <li style="width:100px">locations</li>
     
     <li style="width:100px">source material</li>
</ul>  

</div> 

<ul id="poptab">
<li class="active">
<h4>description</h4>

<p>raised to believe she's the daughter of two prominent hackers in the matrix, Clary was born after her mother had escaped imprisonment & made it to the human Resistance settlement of Zion. Her father rejected the red pill, choosing to instead stay in the Matrix with her older brother even while rejecting the simulated reality around him. the split in the family was hard, & Clary was raised to believe her mother could never re-enter the Matrix for fear of her father finding her, & having her reinserted. 

<p>growing up with access to Zion's archives, Clary knew from a young age that she had some sort of strange talent that no other potential operator possessed - she could manipulate the <b>construct</b> with ease, going on to expand it & craft it in the form that all operators would go on to use but even more impressive, if perhaps a touch alarming, is her ability to maniplate the Matrix itself. she can only take on little changes - a touch her, a change there - without alerting the Matrix' sentinel programs to her presence, & if she were to ever be discovered, the consequences would be dire.

<p>she's hiding a secret though, one that she learned from the single time she's ventured into the Matrix while her crew was asleep. Clary isn't human - she's a bridge. originally existing in the Matrix as a complex program, her consciousness was downloaded into a human body & allowed to be born into the human world. this knowledge carries a heavy burden, but it explains her unique abilities to manipulate & change the programming of the matrix itself.

<p>she knows that every time she interfaces with the matrix, though, she risks discovery & the machines will do <b>anything</b> to get her back on their side. 

<br>
<br>
<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
</li>
<li>
<h4>notes on interaction</h4>

<p><b>option i.</b> <i>meeting after rescue</i>.
<blockquote>
    <p>as the operator of one of the hoverships, Clary is one of the first points of contact a newly rescued redpill would have as their body recovers from their rescue. she's trained with medical knowledge, & some other basic skills to help ease their transition into the real world.
</blockquote>

<p><b>option ii.</b> <i>meeting in the Matrix</i>.
<blockquote>
    <p>no one quite understands or knows how it's possible, but Clary possesses a unique ability to cast herself into the Matrix without an injector port. it takes tremendous effort, & carries even greater risk for her than typical crew owing to her father's presence residing in the Matrix so it's not something she does lightly or often - but it remains something she can use as a last ditch option for an emergency.
</blockquote>

<p><b>option iii.</b> <i>meeting in Zion</i>.
<blockquote>
    <p>should a human be rescued by another hovercraft & their crew, Clary & the Finalizer periodically dock in Zion to refuel & grab supplies.
</blockquote>

<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
</li>

<li>
<h4>headcanons</h4>

<p>- clary's unique abilities come from her exposure to machine & matrix program influence before she was born, priming her human body to accept her programmed consciousness. her father offered up both of his children as experiments to <b>the architect</b> in an effort to find a balance to the equation & keep the Matrix from failing. 
    <blockquote>
        <p>- because of this, Jocelyn doesn't realize that her escape was purposefully engineered in the hopes that her unborn child would act as a counterweight to the older child who remained in the Matrix, with both acting as anchorpoints for their different worlds.
    </blockquote>

<br />
<br />

</li>

