<ul id="poptab">
<li class="active">
<h4>description</h4>

<p>no one really knows much about how clary came to be a guest in Kings Landing or a lady the Queen's services, but her recommendations were superb, & she was adequately vouched for by <b>House Rykker</b> in a bid to regain some social standing within the court. In theory, she was a good candidate for keeping the princess in line when she wasn't with her governess - in practice, it's all a bit more complicated than that. 

<p>Clary & her mother fled Essos before she was even born with the help of <b>Varys</b>, crossing the Narrow Sea to land in Duskendale. Jocelyn would eventually give birth to Clary, & the two of them would be invited as guests to King's Landing. In the aftermath of Robert's Rebellion, Jocelyn was able to fly under the radar & establish herself as a valuable ally in the queen's service. Eventually, her daughter would follow - raised alongside Myrcella as an older playmate to the princess.

<p>Like her mother, Clary would eventually fall into Varys' service, becoming one of his Little Birds.

<br>
<br>
<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
</li>
<li>
<h4>notes on interaction</h4>

<p><b>option i.</b> <i>meeting in King's Landing</i>
<blockquote>
    <p>Clary came to King's Landing when she was very young, & has spent most of her life there in service as a playmate to Princess Myrcella. She can often be found in various places within the Red Keep - her favorites are the Godswood & the various libraries, but she's also intimately familiar with the secret passages throughout the Keep.
</blockquote>

<p><b>option ii.</b> <i>meeting in the city proper.</i>
<blockquote>
    <p>As a lady in the princess' services, Clary very rarely <i>officially</i> sets foot in the city, but sometimes needs must, & she's quite familiar with the Street of Looms, Street of Seeds, & Street of Flour.
</blockquote>

<p><b>option iii.</b> <i>in winterfell</i>
<blockquote>
    <p>Given her status as a lady in Myrcella Baratheon's service, she's part of the household that travels North with the King & his family.
</blockquote>

<p><b>option iv.</b> <i>meeting in another city</i>.
<blockquote>
    <p>In the event that Clary is sent away from King's Landing, it's possible she & her mother would venture to any number of other cities within Westeros so this option is always available with plotting. 
</blockquote>

<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
</li>

<li>
<h4>headcanons</h4>

<p>- Clary is wholly unaware of her brother, who is <a href="https://affcgato.tumblr.com/post/651747955764838400/asshai-under-the-shadow-fandom-verse-jonathan">very much alive & well in Essos</a>. 

<p>- like her brother, Clary is a descendent of the Dragonlords - one of the noble families from the Valyrian Freehold. she is also unaware of this fact, as she takes after her mother & lacks any significant features that would identify her as such.
<blockquote>
    <p>this is further supported by the canon fact that after four hundred years, the surviving Valyrian colonists in the Free Cities have intermingled with the local populations to such an extent that they no longer exist as a major, distinct group anyway.
</blockquote>

<p>- Because she & Jonathan both are descendants of one of the other Dragonlord families in pre-Doom Old Valyria, they have no relation to Daenerys, but there's a sense of implied loyalty given the shared history of their people.

<p>- like her brother, Clary was also victim to her father's experimentations on her before she was born. she's unaware of this, or what it could mean for her. 

<br />
<br />

</li>

