<ul id="poptab">
<li class="active">
<h4>description</h4>

<blockquote>
<p>notes: verse defaults to chapter 1, with chapter 2 compliance available with plotting
</blockquote>

<p>Not even New York was safe enough. After fleeing her family home for Paris & then from there to New York, it seemed like Jocelyn Fairchild still could not escape the ghost of a husband she swore couldn’t possibly be dead. nevertheless, they eked out a life in Brooklyn for a while until a chance sighting of Valentine’s associates near their apartment spooked Jocelyn. taking the advice of an old friend, Jocelyn went off the grid shortly before Clary's sixth birthday, disappearing into the heart of Maine. 

<p>Derry itself wasn’t anything to write home about & that’s precisely why Jocelyn figured it would be safe enough for them to live in anonymity. she took up work as a secretary at the women’s health clinic, with Luke slotting himself into a job running a used book store - Back Pages. for a while, everything way fine.

<p>at least until people started disappearing, making Jocelyn wonder if maybe this quiet little town was just as dangerous as the man they were trying to hide from.

<br>
<br>
