<ul id="poptab">
<li class="active">
<p><h4>description</h4>

<p>several years after the world has gone to hell, Clary works at one of the last outposts for survivors. while some have gone quiet, squeezing out survival in silence, a small group of survivors have shot in the other direction. converting a factory into their living dpace, they've learned that <b>noise</b> is the best defense against most of these creatures, but it comes at a heavy cost. 

<p>they're losing people every year, & supplies are getting harder, & harder to find.

<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
</li>

<li>
<p><h4>notes</h4>

<p>- Clary's old apartment is in one of the most heavily infested parts of the city, & very difficult to get to. It's currently secured, but her medical journals & textbooks - along with a host of other useful books, seeds, & some vague necessary supplies - were never looted out of it when she was brought to the base of operations. She's never been able to go back to get them, either, even thought the need for them is starting to become urgent.

<p>- north district (north of the outpost)

<p>- south district (south of the outpost)

<p>- waterfall camp (secondary camp, one primary source of food). 

<br><br><br><br>

